                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d936">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.48/11</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Thurston</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-30T16:00:00-06:02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 30, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Up to the present time have received your two wireless messages of the 29th [28]
                    and two cablegrams December 27, 1 p.m. and December 27, 6 p.m. only.</p>
                <p>In accordance with contents of wireless message shall now organize relief
                    committee of which I have made Alfred Clark executive officer. Detailed report
                    will be furnished at once when committee at work.</p>
                <p>For the information of Red Cross. The representative of Rockefeller foundation
                    fears epidemics and recommends that mixed typhoid and paravaccine be sent.
                    Shocks continue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
